  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Building Interactive Background**\n\nI\'ve decided to prioritize creating a dedicated `InteractiveBackground.tsx` component within `/src/components/animations/`. The plan now involves establishing a foundational system for the interactive experience, likely focusing on a basic particle canvas, before integrating it with `p5.js`.\n\n\n**Refining p5.js Integration**\n\nI\'m now thinking through the `p5.js` implementation strategy. To avoid potential issues with `react-p5` and ensure stability, I\'m planning a custom sketch in \"Instance Mode.\" This approach will use `useRef` to mount `p5` within a React component. I\'ve got a basic structure outlined in `/src/components/animations/InteractiveBackground.tsx`, and I\'m targeting an interactive mouse trail, floating constellation nodes, and adaptive performance across devices. I\'m exploring the p5 Instance Mode sketch to confirm the right structure.\n\n\n**Implementing Particle Simulation**\n\nNow, I\'m working on the `InteractiveBackground` component, focusing on the `p5.js` integration. I\'ve included a mobile device check and implemented a particle system with adjustable particle count. Each particle is initialized, and now I\'m working to implement its movement and visual behavior.\n\n\n**Developing Particle Physics**\n\nI\'ve got the particle physics in place now, including bouncing behavior off canvas boundaries. Particles are updated and drawn with a deep blue background. I\'m focusing on making the particle interactions more complex and visually appealing now.\n\n\n**Adding Interactive Features**\n\nI\'ve implemented particle connections as nodes, visualized with a violet color, which is dependent on distance. Additionally, I\'ve incorporated mouse interaction, drawing cyan lines to attract particles and create hover-like effects. I\'m focusing on ensuring these additions feel natural and responsive within the interactive background.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create a p5.js-powered background system in `/src/components/animations/InteractiveBackground.tsx`. Using p5\'s instance mode, we fully encapsulate the sketch, configure support for mouse interactivity, render constellation paths, and optimize particle volume for mobile viewports cleanly."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 829581515
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
