  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Finalizing the Summary**\n\nI\'ve confirmed the build\'s success and server restart. Now, I\'m composing a polished and professional summary, adhering precisely to the specified communication guidelines and format. My focus is delivering a refined response, keeping in mind the user\'s preference for premium quality.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the development of the premium, dark-themed interactive portfolio for **Mohamed Irsath Kareem**, tailored with smooth micro-animations, high-fidelity responsive layouts, and a decoupled data architecture.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Aesthetic Style Guidelines (The \"Deep Cosmic\" Slate Theme)\nInspired by the design paradigms of **Linear**, **Vercel**, and **Stripe**, the application is framed entirely around a sleek, immersive dark-mode canvas:\n*   **Palette Coordinates**: Uses a dark midnight base (`#050816`), deep slate surfaces (`#0f172a`), neon cyan highlights (`#38bdf8`), and electric violet accents (`#8b5cf6`).\n*   **Aesthetic Pairings**: Features **Space Grotesk** for clean layout headings, **Inter** for high-density reading copy, and **JetBrains Mono** for simulated code terminals.\n*   **Glassmorphism Borders**: Applied custom blurs, floating container shadows, and responsive glass-panel headers that integrate into the background.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\247\251 Core Architecture & Features Completed\nI built a clean architecture keeping UI layers strictly separate from static domain records:\n\n1.  **Strict Data Separation (Repository Pattern)**:\n    *   No titles or projects are hardcoded directly into components.\n    *   Created structured models (`Profile`, `SkillGroup`, `Project`, `Blog`) and standard interfaces in a central data directory.\n    *   Constructed a unified, thread-safe `PortfolioRepository` singleton which all React views query directly.\n2.  **p5.js Interactive Starfield**:\n    *   Designed a lightweight instance-mode p5.js canvas running globally behind all page viewports.\n    *   Features constellations, drifting floating dots, and interactive mouse gravity trails that warp depending on cursor paths.\n    *   Overhead is optimized and particle count is reduced on mobile screens to preserve browser CPU.\n3.  **Advanced Routing & Split Loading**:\n    *   Configured standard navigation across routes (`Home`, `About`, `Projects`, `Blogs`, `Skills`, `Contact`).\n    *   Integrated dynamic component chunking (`React.lazy()` and `<Suspense>`) to guarantee instant load times.\n    *   Implemented a seamless viewport scroll-restoring module so readers start at the top of each page.\n4.  **Major & Mini Projects Displays**:\n    *   **Major Platforms**: Highlighted *Codehorn* and *NoteMyShow* inside high-density graphical cards detailing specifications.\n    *   **Mini Labs**: Displayed horizontal experiments like *Jetpack Compose Animations* and *Custom Layouts* with tag categorizations and direct GitHub links.\n5.  **Robust Blog Spec Renderer**:\n    *   Supports out-of-box Markdown processing using custom-configured renderers for internal design articles.\n    *   Provides automatic Table of Contents parsing, which scans headers on the fly to yield a sticky nav-index block for easy reading.\n6.  **Interactive Forms & Transitions**:\n    *   Form handles include animated, glowing input lines on focus and robust client-side validations.\n    *   Submitting messages triggers a mock secure cryptographic transmission spinner, culminating in a spring success checkmark.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 163121193
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
