  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Aura Floating Skills**\n\nI\'m now diving into the design of the \"Aura Floating Skills\" section. The goal is to make it visually stunning and incredibly functional, aligning perfectly with the \"Immersive UI\" aesthetic. Think text gradients, glow-blue properties, and visual elements such as glassy effects. I\'m focusing on aesthetics, and functionality. My plan is to start with a list of collective skills that are key.\n\n\n**Crafting Technological Orbit**\n\nI\'m now integrating Kotlin Multiplatform, Spring Boot, Kotlin, Java, and React into a cohesive \"Technological Orbit.\" I\'m aiming for an interactive layout using a block, and incorporating a core competence section. The goal is to highlight cross-platform enterprise microservices and state engines in a visually compelling way, using a glassy UI and text gradients.\n\n\n**Visualizing Orbital Arena**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the orbital arena\'s visual representation, aiming for an immersive experience. I\'m exploring the use of animated dotted rings for an outer orbit effect, with varying speeds and directions. A central sun node, with a gradient background, glow, and hover effects, will be the focus of attention. I\'m working with React and focusing on the appearance, making sure it gives the right impression.\n\n\n**Refining Skill Node Design**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the floating skill node design. I\'m experimenting with animated gradients using tailwind, and positioning using polar coordinates for a circular orbit. I want a glow effect that\'s subtle yet captivating. I also need it to be responsive, so it is an element that can be clicked. The goal is a visually appealing way to select skills that are key.\n\n\n**Implementing Skill Animation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on implementing the skill node animations. I\'m using framer-motion to create subtle, yet captivating, pulsing effects. I\'ve designed the animation to be responsive to the selected state and hover interactions. I\'m leveraging polar coordinates, transition durations, and varying animation behaviors to deliver an engaging visual experience. I\'ve used dynamic positioning within the orbital layout.\n\n\n**Enhancing Node Interactivity**\n\nI\'m now integrating tap effects and hover tooltips for the skill nodes. I\'m using `whileTap` from Framer Motion for a scale effect, and CSS for a subtle connecting line. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and visual feedback, with a tooltip displaying the skill name on hover. The goal is to make the nodes interactive and informative within the orbital layout.\n\n\n**Refining Skill Detail Display**\n\nI\'m now focused on the display of detailed skill metrics. I\'m aiming for a visually clean and informative layout. I\'m using a responsive grid with CSS, and a glassy panel. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and visual balance. The layout includes a custom icon. I\'m using the selected skill index to display the details. I\'m looking to make it a great experience.\n\n\n**Detailing Skill Metrics Display**\n\nI\'m now implementing the skill details display, using a custom layout. I\'m focusing on incorporating the current design. I\'m leveraging Tailwind classes and dynamic content to present skill tags, names, levels, and long descriptions. The aim is to make a visual presentation for the details, using a glassy UI and level indicators. I\'m also including associated architecture and concepts.\n\n\n**Integrating Skill Navigation**\n\nI\'m now integrating the navigation buttons. I\'m focusing on making a complete experience for navigation. My goal is a visually appealing and intuitive flow. I\'m leveraging CSS classes and click handlers to navigate between the skills, with updated indexes. I\'m ensuring smooth transitions and responsiveness.\n\n\n**Mapping Icon Representation**\n\nI\'m now mapping icons to represent the skills. I\'ve chosen `Smartphone`, `Layers`, `Cpu`, `Server`, and `Code2` for Jetpack Compose, Compose Multiplatform, Kotlin Multiplatform, Spring Boot, and Kotlin, respectively. The focus is to choose icons that map to the underlying architecture, with a beautiful display.\n\n\n"
